<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by nepolon on 08-22-2001 03:32 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Let me begin by saying that I very much appreciate the work that goes into the maps.  I have benefited from your maps and would like to continue to do so.

I have used your Amazon.com affiliation link to drop a little change in your pocket already, and would consider subsidy by route of PayPal or whatever, to Allakhazam on your behalf.

begin rant::
I'm not suggesting you scrap anything, but you need to ask yourself what it is about this site that you WANT to keep working on, even if only at a slower pace.  Everything else should probably be dumped.

All the BS aside, do you want to make the maps?  You say you do.  Than make the maps.  

Now repeat this question and answer for each major aspect of this site... If your dissatisfying time is *really* spent in replying to thousands of emails, consider why you do it.

I have been on the web too long, so my opinions are not necessarily popular, but here goes.  

It spoils folks to be able to throw up a website and sit back (not literally, but figuratively) and "watch the money roll in." (Yes, I know it was never like that, but that isn't the point.) 

Yes, I am saying you sound like a spoiled brat by complaining about the soft market for banners, links, etc.  If you want to make easy money on the web, do porn--if you want to do something useful than accept the fact that you won't make much of a living off of maintaining an ordinary website alone (meaning a website NOT associated with a separate business/product/whatever).

And yes, I am especially cynical; if it is any consolation I am a self-employed software and web developer by trade, an open-source zealot by faith, and have spent a sizable chunk of my own change building, maintaining, and subsidizing websites I have created for off-work purposes.  I dont feel like the users of those sites owe me anything for the work of creating or maintaining them.  The only cost I can justify passing along is the cost of hosting, but if you have that taken care of I don't understand what you think you are owed.

::end rant
Steve</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
